title: US at crossroads in handling of Netanyahu government's 'violent' rhetoric
description: The United States finds itself in an increasingly delicate position as it works to continue supporting one of its staunchest allies in Israel while also drawing a firm line in condemning far-right leaders in Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's government calling for widespread violence against Palestinians.

title: US contractor killed and five service members wounded in likely Iranian-made UAV attack in Syria: Pentagon
description: The United States launched airstrikes in Syria after a U.S. contractor was killed and five U.S. service members and an additional contractor were injured from a one-way unmanned aerial vehicle attack believed to be Iranian-made, the Department of Defense announced Thursday.

title: UK deputy prime minister resigns after bullying allegations
description: United Kingdom Deputy Prime Minister Dominic Raab resigned from his position following allegations of bullying, he announced on Friday.

title: Rwanda flooding: More than 100 killed in natural disaster
description: At least 109 people are dead in western Rwanda after heavy rain caused massive flooding in the region early Wednesday morning, according to authorities.

title: At least 58 people dead in South Africa building fire
description: At least 58 people have died in a fire at a building in Johannesburg, South Africa, authorities said on Thursday.
